16/02 11:34:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Fair GM?</span><hr size=1> This is something happened yesterday on our Server Povar. It was a normal dispute between 2 guilds and Povar's lead GM came to resolve the issue from 1 party's petition. I won't get into the detail of that. Although the other guild had no respect for player convention of camping for epic quest mobs nor had any qalms about lying to GM during their petition about what happened, the head GM of Povar pretty much stick strictly by the book and resolved that dispute, even if he didn't really listen to the defense's side of story.<br>However, the issue I want to raise here is that. When a GM tell someone one thing and then does another, and then denying what he has done wrong, should he still be a server's lead GM? <br><br>Here is what happened after the dispute. Our wizard from the dispute was to be punished by rolling back his charater so that he will lose his epic. Povar's lead GM Karnillem told him that his charater will be rolled back to previous day's save point and he will reimburse any item lost to trade before that.<br><br>Quoate from him in log: &quot;[Sun Apr 14 17:19:36 2002] Karnillem says, 4) you are being resored to the preivious day when you had the staffs and the sprcket you are still currently holding.'&quot;<br>&quot;[Sun Apr 14 17:33:13 2002] Karnillem tells you, 'You will be being restored back to a previous save. anything you will have worked on since yesturday will be lost. I Did Copy your trade log so I Can reimburs the items you recieved up till this point.'&quot;<br>&quot;[Sun Apr 14 18:59:39 2002] You told Karnillem, 'woah so my ring earing xp gone?'<br>[Sun Apr 14 19:00:00 2002] Karnillem tells you, 'I gave you everything we had in the logs.'<br>[Sun Apr 14 19:00:22 2002] You told Karnillem, 'This rollback is 5 days old how far back did you pull logs?'<br>[Sun Apr 14 19:00:30 2002] Karnillem tells you, '14 days'<br>[Sun Apr 14 19:00:45 2002] You told Karnillem, 'then you missed ALOT of stuff'<br>[Sun Apr 14 19:00:47 2002] Karnillem tells you, 'and reimbursed everything from the 10th'<br>[Sun Apr 14 19:01:04 2002] You told Karnillem, 'but rollback is from the 8th'<br>[Sun Apr 14 19:02:45 2002] You told Karnillem, 'everything I'm missing is stuff I looted'<br>[Sun Apr 14 19:02:54 2002] You told Karnillem, 'since it's all no drop'<br>[Sun Apr 14 19:03:21 2002] Karnillem tells you, 'nothing in my loot logs my friend'<br>[Sun Apr 14 19:03:31 2002] You told Karnillem, 'that's impossible'<br>[Sun Apr 14 19:03:57 2002] Karnillem tells you, 'good luck my friend'<br>[Sun Apr 14 19:04:04 2002] You told Karnillem, '[queued], WAIT! '&quot;<br><br>Not only he did not roll back the char to the previous day as he said, he insisted on the roll back was correct while a number of people can atest to the roll back is indeed from the an earlier date because that's when our wizard completed his Emperor Key ( Ring of Shissar ). So all the item the wizard looted from the old roll back date that Karnillem insisted was correct and from previous day are missing and he will not reimburse those items. Other loot are just loot. But Emp key is more then 60 hours of camping and now it's gone waste for no good reason other then Karnillem refusing to admit that he made a mistake and refusing to correct it. Making a poor judgement and going strictly by policy is understandable. Making a clear mistake and refusing to correct the mistake for a server lead GM imho is not acceptable.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxodduzz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xodduzz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/02 11:48:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fair GM?</span><hr size=1> /em points at rule number 1 of this board...<br><br>Rant Attention Posts – Threads that are rants based on getting Verants attention since “we’re the only message board that Verant reads” should be locked immediately. Reply to the thread<br><br>“The appropriate place to send Verant feedback for any class balance issues is feedback@verant.com”<br><br>-It looks to me as that was the idea.. sorry if I've mistaken... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uthorilan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>thorilan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/17/02 1:26:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fair GM?</span><hr size=1> i personaly would use a spellcheck and organize your sentances and then make a official email letter with a little more clerification on some things to several departments at sony. if it is well thought out and planned you have a shot but posting here is probly not a good idea. though if you put it in the rants forum or some other similar forum somewhere else that would have been better judgement imho <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uyanabanana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>YanaBanana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/17/02 3:26:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Rant</span><hr size=1> Yeah I realize this is not the best place to post. The point is really to get more people exposed to and read about what happened. Which is why I posted on here and wiz site. The wizard involved is emailing to VI regardling this issue since he is the direct party effected by action discribed. I however feel compelled to do something, such as posting like I have done, in some minor way to gain some public opinion or support that might influence VI to do something about what happened. If I only post it in the rant section, it will be read by very few imho. If I violated forum rules for doing so, I appologize. However, I feel strongly enough to want to spread the word so to speak even if I have to violate a few forum rules to do so. There are times when something wrong is done and someone went too far, and in this case it is one of them. If the moderator feel this thread needs to be locked or removed, feel free to do so.<br>  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utibishatter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TibisHatter</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.top-hat.demon.co.uk/Images/10x10.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/17/02 3:48:05 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.top-hat.demon.co.uk/Images/TibHdSoL.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rant</span><hr size=1> You shouldn't have crossposted it to the Main Lounge.  What you should have done is email <a href="mailto:mods@thesafehouse.org">mods@thesafehouse.org</a> and asked for your original thread to be moved.<br><br>I have moved the original thread to the Rant Hall (where is was better suited anyway) and I'm going to lock this. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showPrevMessage?topicID=23335.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com